<div class="abt-ct container mt-4 mb-4">
  <h1>About Coin Rankings Project</h1>

  <h2>1. Gathering and Storing Data</h2>

  <h3>1.1 Describing Datasets</h3>

  <div class="p-3 bg-light">
    <h4>Coin Rankings API:</h4>
    <p><strong>Description:</strong> The Coin Ranking API provides real-time and historical data on various cryptocurrencies. This includes details such as the name, symbol, market cap, price, and volume of each cryptocurrency.</p>

    <h5>Required Databases and Columns:</h5>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Cryptocurrencies table:</strong>
        <ul>
          <li>id: primary key</li>
          <li>name: string</li>
          <li>symbol: string</li>
          <li>market_cap: decimal</li>
          <li>price: decimal</li>
          <li>volume_24h: decimal</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li><strong>Historical Prices table:</strong>
        <ul>
          <li>id: primary key</li>
          <li>price: decimal</li>
          <li>datetime: datetime</li>
          <li>cryptocurrency_id: foreign key</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="p-3 bg-light mt-4">
    <h4>Faker Gem:</h4>
    <p><strong>Description:</strong> The Faker gem is used to generate fake data for users and their wallets. This includes usernames, emails, wallet names, and associations with cryptocurrencies.</p>

    <h5>Required Databases and Columns:</h5>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Users table:</strong>
        <ul>
          <li>id: primary key</li>
          <li>name: string</li>
          <li>email: string</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li><strong>Wallets table:</strong>
        <ul>
          <li>id: primary key</li>
          <li>name: string</li>
          <li>user_id: foreign key</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li><strong>Wallet Cryptocurrencies table:</strong>
        <ul>
          <li>id: primary key</li>
          <li>wallet_id: foreign key</li>
          <li>cryptocurrency_id: foreign key</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="p-3 bg-light mt-4">
    <h4>CSV File for Exchange Data:</h4>
    <p><strong>Description:</strong> This CSV file contains data on various cryptocurrency exchanges, including their names and websites.</p>

    <h5>Required Database Tables and Columns:</h5>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Exchanges table:</strong>
        <ul>
          <li>id: primary key</li>
          <li>name: string</li>
          <li>website_url: string</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li><strong>Cryptocurrency Exchanges table:</strong>
        <ul>
          <li>id: primary key</li>
          <li>cryptocurrency_id: foreign key</li>
          <li>exchange_id: foreign key</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 class="mt-4">Integration and Relationships:</h2>
  <ul class="integration">
    <li>The <strong>cryptocurrencies table</strong> will store data pulled from the Coin Ranking API.</li>
    <li>The <strong>historical_prices table</strong> will store historical price data for each cryptocurrency.</li>
    <li>The <strong>exchanges table</strong> will store data from the CSV file, representing various cryptocurrency exchanges.</li>
    <li>The <strong>cryptocurrency_exchanges table</strong> will create a many-to-many relationship between cryptocurrencies and exchanges.</li>
    <li>The <strong>users table</strong> will store user data generated by the Faker gem.</li>
    <li>The <strong>wallets table</strong> will store wallet data for each user, also generated by Faker.</li>
    <li>The <strong>wallet_cryptocurrencies table</strong> will create a many-to-many relationship between wallets and cryptocurrencies.</li>
  </ul>

